Dental_Ishika_Raymond - Temporary Dental Staffing Platform
CSC309 A3 - Installation Guide

=== Environment ===

Tested on Ubuntu 22.04 with Node.js v18+ and npm v9+.
The backend and frontend can run on the same machine.

=== Prerequisites ===

  Node.js v18+  https://nodejs.org/
  npm v9+

All other dependencies are listed in backend/package.json and frontend/package.json and are installed automatically via npm install.

Backend packages: express, cors, bcrypt, multer, socket.io, jsonwebtoken, express-jwt, uuid, prisma, @prisma/client, sqlite3, dotenv

Frontend packages: react, react-dom, react-router-dom, axios, socket.io-client, vite, tailwindcss, postcss, autoprefixer

=== Local Setup ===

1. Backend

  cd backend
  npm install
  npx prisma generate
  npm run seed        # creates dev.db and populates demo data
  node src/server.js 3000

  The server listens on port 3000. Demo accounts (all passwords: 123123):
    admin1@csc309.utoronto.ca
    business1@csc309.utoronto.ca  (through business12@...)
    regular1@csc309.utoronto.ca   (through regular22@...)

2. Frontend

  cd frontend
  npm install
  npm run dev

  Starts on http://localhost:5173. The Vite dev server proxies API requests to localhost:3000 so no extra configuration is needed for local development.

=== Deployment (Railway) ===

The app is deployed as two services on Railway (https://railway.app) from a GitHub repository - one for the backend and one for the frontend. Both services point to the same repo but use different root directories.

Backend service:
  Root directory: backend
  Start command:  npm start
  Environment variable:
    FRONTEND_URL=<deployed frontend URL>   (set after frontend is deployed)

  The start command automatically runs prisma db push and seeds the database on each start,
  so no manual database setup is required after deployment.

Frontend service:
  Root directory:  frontend
  Build command:   npm run build
  Start command:   npm run serve
  Environment variable:
    VITE_API_URL=<deployed backend URL>

  Note: VITE_API_URL must be set before the first build - Vite bakes it into the compiled bundle at build time, not at runtime.
  Note: frontend/railway.json is included to override Railway's (Railpack) install command to "npm install" instead of "npm ci", avoiding a lock file compatibility error with Railway's Linux build environment. If the build still fails with a lock file error, override it manually in Railway Settings -> Build -> Install Command -> npm install.

After both services are running:
  - Update FRONTEND_URL on the backend service to match the frontend URL

SQLite note: Railway uses an ephemeral filesystem, so the database resets on each redeploy. The seed runs automatically on each start, so no manual action is needed after redeployment. Uploaded files (avatars, resumes) are also ephemeral and lost on redeploy.

To reset the local database:
  rm -f backend/prisma/dev.db backend/prisma/dev.db-journal
  cd backend && npx prisma db push && npm run seed
